e-mail: promed@usa.healthnet.org
[Most of these cases are certainly cholera. The International Center for
Diarrheal Diseases Research which is now seeing 500 cases a day is a
world-famous cholera research center, and its annual reports regularly
report the isolation of cholera from cases in Bangladesh. But because the
country fears a ban on its shrimp exports, it steadfastly refuses to admit
that the disease occurs, or to report it to WHO as required by the
International Health Regulations. It even supposedly claims that 64,000
cases is not an epidemic (see above).
Perhaps it will now follow the lead of Thailand, and start to admit that,
yes, it does have cases of _Vibrio cholerae_ infection, even if they are
not going to call it cholera yet -- see:
